    • getMessageReplayCheckerBeanName

      @Nullable public String getMessageReplayCheckerBeanName()
      Refers to a MessageReplayChecker bean that will be used by the application to detect message replay attacks. If not set, a DefaultMessageReplayChecker will be used.
      Specified by:
      getMessageReplayCheckerBeanName in interface SignServiceConfigurationProperties
      Returns:
      the bean name or null
      See Also:
      • SignServiceConfigurationProperties.getReplayCheckerStorageContainerBeanName()

    • getReplayCheckerStorageContainerBeanName

      @Nullable public String getReplayCheckerStorageContainerBeanName()
      Relevant only if message-replay-checker-bean-name is not set. In these cases a DefaultMessageReplayChecker will be created using a ReplayCheckerStorageContainer instance. This setting refers to ReplayCheckerStorageContainer bean.

      If this setting is null an InMemoryReplayCheckerStorageContainer instance will be used. This is not advisable in a distributed application setup (i.e., when several instances of the SignService application is running).

      Specified by:
      getReplayCheckerStorageContainerBeanName in interface SignServiceConfigurationProperties
      Returns:
      the bean name of null
